BEGIN:VCALENDAR
VERSION:2.0
PRODID:-//fostercrisis.com//Pledge Calendar//EN
CALSCALE:GREGORIAN
METHOD:PUBLISH
X-WR-CALNAME:Foster Crisis — Weekly Prayer
X-WR-CALDESC:A weekly Sunday-morning meditation on the 329,000 children in American foster care tonight — scripture, prompt, and one action.
REFRESH-INTERVAL;VALUE=DURATION:P1D
X-PUBLISHED-TTL:P1D
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260426@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260426T090000
DTEND:20260426T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · Be doers of the word
DESCRIPTION:"Pure religion before God the Father is this: to visit orphans 
 and widows in their affliction\, and to keep oneself unstained from the wo
 rld." — James 1:27\n\n329\,000 American children are in foster care tonigh
 t. 70\,418 are waiting for a forever family. Has God asked you to open you
 r home?\n\nfostercrisis.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260503@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260503T090000
DTEND:20260503T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · Children are a heritage
DESCRIPTION:"Behold\, children are a heritage from the Lord\, the fruit of 
 the womb a reward. Blessed is the man who fills his quiver with them." — P
 salm 127:3\, 5\n\nWhat heritage has the American Church left the 329\,000 
 children in foster care tonight?\n\nfostercrisis.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260510@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260510T090000
DTEND:20260510T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · Let the children come
DESCRIPTION:"Let the little children come to me\, and do not hinder them\, 
 for to such belongs the kingdom of heaven." — Matthew 19:14\n\nThere is a 
 child in your state tonight whose case file lists exactly zero adults will
 ing to open their door. The kingdom belongs to her.\n\nfostercrisis.com/#s
 olution
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260517@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260517T090000
DTEND:20260517T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · The Lord is near the brokenhearted
DESCRIPTION:"The Lord is near to the brokenhearted and saves the crushed in
  spirit." — Psalm 34:18\n\nToday\, one in four 17-year-olds in California 
 foster care has already attempted suicide. Pray that every caseworker\, ju
 dge\, and foster parent they meet this week is the one God uses to draw ne
 ar.\n\nfostercrisis.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260524@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260524T090000
DTEND:20260524T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · Proclaim liberty to the captives
DESCRIPTION:"The Spirit of the Lord God is upon me ... to proclaim liberty 
 to the captives\, and the opening of the prison to those who are bound." —
  Isaiah 61:1\n\nOne in five U.S. prison inmates is a former foster child. 
 The cheapest crime-reduction program in America is a spare bedroom.\n\nfos
 tercrisis.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260531@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260531T090000
DTEND:20260531T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · Where your treasure is
DESCRIPTION:"Where your treasure is\, there your heart will also be." — Mat
 thew 6:21\n\nThe average American Christian gives 2.8% of their income to 
 the church and spends seven hours a day on a screen. What if your heart we
 nt where a child's home could be?\n\nfostercrisis.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260607@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260607T090000
DTEND:20260607T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · What Jesus did at the grave
DESCRIPTION:"Jesus wept." — John 11:35\n\nHundreds of thousands of American
  foster children and alumni have died early over the last four decades who
  would still be alive if they had had a home. Weep with him. Then act.\n\n
 fostercrisis.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260614@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260614T090000
DTEND:20260614T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · He heals all your diseases
DESCRIPTION:"Bless the Lord\, O my soul ... who forgives all your iniquity\
 , who heals all your diseases\, who redeems your life from the pit." — Psa
 lm 103:2–4\n\n80% of foster youth enter adulthood with a mental-health dis
 order. 20 million living Americans carry the scars. Pray for the ones stil
 l in the pit.\n\nfostercrisis.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260621@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260621T090000
DTEND:20260621T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · Justice like an ever-flowing stream
DESCRIPTION:"I hate\, I despise your feasts ... But let justice roll down l
 ike waters\, and righteousness like an ever-flowing stream." — Amos 5:21\,
  24\n\nRed-state foster-care rates average 41% higher than blue-state. The
  geography of Christian identity overlaps the geography of Christian failu
 re. Pray. Then open the door.\n\nfostercrisis.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260628@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260628T090000
DTEND:20260628T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · Visit the orphan
DESCRIPTION:"Defend the weak and the fatherless\; uphold the cause of the p
 oor and the oppressed." — Psalm 82:3\n\nTonight\, a teenager in your state
  will age out of foster care with no family. This is the week you could ca
 ll the agency.\n\nfostercrisis.com/#solution
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260705@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260705T090000
DTEND:20260705T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · Repent and renew
DESCRIPTION:"Renew your Church\, O Lord\, beginning with me." — A prayer of
  repentance\n\nThe American Church built megachurches\, branded merchandis
 e\, and political coalitions while the orphan waited at its doorstep for f
 orty years. Pray for renewal that begins with a phone call.\n\nfostercrisi
 s.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260712@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260712T090000
DTEND:20260712T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · 380\,000 churches · 34\,817 children
DESCRIPTION:There are roughly 380\,000 Christian congregations in the Unite
 d States. 34\,817 children are legally free for adoption tonight.\n\nIf on
 e family in every eleven churches said yes\, the waitlist would end by Chr
 istmas. Pray that you are the one family in your church.\n\nfostercrisis.c
 om
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260719@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260719T090000
DTEND:20260719T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · A house built on rock
DESCRIPTION:"Everyone then who hears these words of mine and does them will
  be like a wise man who built his house on the rock." — Matthew 7:24\n\nTh
 e house that matters is not the one on your mortgage. It is the one that b
 ecomes a home for a child who has never had one.\n\nfostercrisis.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260726@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260726T090000
DTEND:20260726T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · The sparrow and the hair
DESCRIPTION:"Are not two sparrows sold for a penny? And not one of them wil
 l fall to the ground apart from your Father." — Matthew 10:29–31\n\nYou nu
 mber every hair and every sparrow. You did not lose count of the children 
 the state took. Make us count them too.\n\nfostercrisis.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260802@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260802T090000
DTEND:20260802T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · To the least of these
DESCRIPTION:"Truly\, I say to you\, as you did it to one of the least of th
 ese my brothers\, you did it to me." — Matthew 25:40\n\nThe least of these
  in your state has a caseworker\, a file number\, and a bed assignment tha
 t changes every few months. Christ is wearing her face this week.\n\nfoste
 rcrisis.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260809@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260809T090000
DTEND:20260809T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · Do justice\, love mercy
DESCRIPTION:"He has told you\, O man\, what is good\; and what does the Lor
 d require of you but to do justice\, and to love kindness\, and to walk hu
 mbly with your God?" — Micah 6:8\n\nJustice here has a street address: you
 r local Department of Child and Family Services. This is the week to look 
 up the phone number.\n\nfostercrisis.com/#solution
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260816@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260816T090000
DTEND:20260816T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · The unborn and the born
DESCRIPTION:Why fight so hard for the unborn — only to abandon the born?\n\
 n329\,000 American children are in foster care tonight. Roughly 34 of them
  will die this year above the general-population rate. Prayerfully conside
 r opening your home.\n\nfostercrisis.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260823@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260823T090000
DTEND:20260823T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · Send me
DESCRIPTION:"And I heard the voice of the Lord saying\, 'Whom shall I send\
 , and who will go for us?' Then I said\, 'Here I am! Send me.'" — Isaiah 6
 :8\n\nThe foster agency in your state has been waiting for someone to walk
  through the door. Let this week's prayer be the same one Isaiah prayed.\n
 \nfostercrisis.com/#solution
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260830@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260830T090000
DTEND:20260830T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · A home and a name
DESCRIPTION:"I will give\, in my house and within my walls\, a monument and
  a name better than sons and daughters\; I will give them an everlasting n
 ame that shall not be cut off." — Isaiah 56:5\n\nA foster child in your st
 ate tonight has no permanent address and a name almost no one knows. The k
 ingdom of God is shaped like a home with their name on the door.\n\nfoster
 crisis.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:pledge-20260906@fostercrisis.com
DTSTAMP:20260423T013715Z
DTSTART:20260906T090000
DTEND:20260906T092000
SUMMARY:Foster Crisis · No more death\, no more tears
DESCRIPTION:"He will wipe away every tear from their eyes\, and death shall
  be no more\, neither shall there be mourning\, nor crying\, nor pain anym
 ore." — Revelation 21:4\n\nUntil then\, the Church is the arms that hold t
 hem in the waiting. Be the arms.\n\nfostercrisis.com
URL;VALUE=URI:https://fostercrisis.com/#solution
CATEGORIES:Foster Crisis,Prayer
END:VEVENT
